	•	Provide third parties with direct interactive access to the Software
	•	Rebrand, bundle, or market the Software as a standalone product or platform

⸻

4. Configuration Files

You may modify, extend, and adapt Configuration Files for use with the Software.

You may share Configuration Files independently of the Software, provided they do not include or redistribute the Software itself.

Unless explicitly authorised by the author, Configuration Files may not be used as part of a competing commercial product, hosted service, or managed offering.

⸻

5. Author-Provided Data Files

You may use Author-Provided Data Files solely in connection with the Software.

Unless explicitly authorised by the author, Author-Provided Data Files may not be redistributed independently of the Software or used as part of a competing commercial product, hosted service, or managed offering.

